This paper discusses the performance of meta-learning algorithms, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper specifically focuses on the Model Agnostic Meta Learning (MAML) algorithm, which is used in reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also mentions computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) as potential applications of meta-learning, making them less likely but still possible sub-categories.
